{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ce2d626a-3fdb-4d53-845a-2f03908fd020","content":"Here's what needs to change:\n\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Replace** the separate `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package with the unified `MSTest` v3 meta-package (it bundles the test SDK, framework, and adapter)\n\nThe test code itself (`[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `Assert.*`) is compatible as-is.\n\nLet me apply the changes:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Kg8U4uhEp7493F1VhKpEzd","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Upgrading to MSTest v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Tt6i7tBMq5NQdQx86W8Xev","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-8a457a78688f4889ad6afb5a8b2f1908/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.5.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-8a457a78688f4889ad6afb5a8b2f1908/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"1979bb64-29ec-4bf3-be9c-cc9d2ac98543","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has:\n1. A `.csproj` targeting `net462` with an assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` 17.5.0\n3. Test code using `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace\n\nTo upgrade to MSTest v3:\n1. Remove the assembly `<Reference>` to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. Add `<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.x.x\" />` (MSTest v3 is a meta-package that includes MSTest.TestFramework, MSTest.TestAdapter, and Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk)\n\n\n3. The namespace stays the same, so no test code changes needed, and their current target framework of .NET Framework 4.6.2 already meets MSTest v3's minimum requirements.\n4. For the version, I'll go with MSTest 3.6.x as a reasonable stable release for April 2026.\n5. The key simplification is that the MSTest meta-package bundles everything together, so I can remove the old assembly reference and consolidate the package references in the project file.\n\nLet me just make these changes and test the build to ensure everything works correctly.","outputTokens":1067,"requestId":"0434:13D1C8:55D893:652FFF:69E82F63"},"id":"f41d2194-039b-4c3a-8946-b0a83d4f1de0","timestamp":"2026-04-22T02:16:21.859Z","parentId":"fb7420c2-fb4a-4e43-b65d-1ff8f1da0a25"}
